# Cline Rules — Immich Docker Deployment

## Context
This is an Immich (self-hosted photo manager) deployment using Docker Compose on macOS.
The project lives at `$PROJECT_DIR` (set by the scripts dynamically).

## Core Constraints
1. **NEVER run `docker compose up -d` without `--pull never`** — Docker cannot reach `ghcr.io` from this network due to TLS timeout in its internal proxy.
2. **DO NOT modify `./library/` or `./postgres/` manually** — Immich manages these internally.
3. **The docker-compose.yml has `@sha256:` digests stripped** — keep them removed or images won't match.
4. **Timezone is `America/La_Paz`** — do not change without user consent.
5. **Images are tagged as `:release`** (not `:latest` or `:v2`).

## Image Pulling Workflow (when needed)
If new images are needed from ghcr.io:
```bash
python3 AI/pull-images.py ghcr.io immich-app/immich-server release
python3 AI/pull-images.py ghcr.io immich-app/immich-machine-learning release
python3 AI/pull-images.py ghcr.io immich-app/postgres 14-vectorchord0.4.3-pgvectors0.2.0
# valkey pulls from Docker Hub (works fine):
docker pull docker.io/valkey/valkey:9
```
Then tag and start:
```bash
docker tag <id> ghcr.io/immich-app/<name>:release
docker compose up -d --pull never
```

## Backup & Restore (S3)

### Backup (upload to S3)
```bash
python3 backup-to-s3.py              # Full: photos + DB + config
python3 backup-to-s3.py --dry-run    # Preview only
python3 backup-to-s3.py --db-only    # Database only
python3 backup-to-s3.py --lib-only   # Photos only
```
Uploads to `s3://$S3_BUCKET/` (from `.env`):
- `library/` → photos (incremental, skips unchanged)
- `database/` → pg_dump SQL gzipped (keeps last 7)
- `config/` → .env, docker-compose.yml, pull-images.py

### Restore (from S3 to new machine)
```bash
python3 restore-from-s3.py              # Full restore
python3 restore-from-s3.py --dry-run    # Preview only
python3 restore-from-s3.py --skip-pull  # Skip image download
```
Downloads config from S3 first (fallback to GitHub), pulls images, syncs photos, restores DB, starts Immich.

## Project Structure
```
immich/
├── docker-compose.yml        # 4 services
├── .env                      # UPLOAD_LOCATION, DB_PASSWORD, TZ, IMMICH_VERSION
├── backup-to-s3.py           # 🔄 Backup → S3 (photos + DB + config)
├── restore-from-s3.py        # 🔥 Disaster recovery ← S3
├── library/                  # Uploaded photos (Immich-managed, DO NOT TOUCH)
├── postgres/                 # Database files (Immich-managed, DO NOT TOUCH)
└── AI/                       # Documentation & tools
    ├── immich-knowledge.md
    ├── disaster-recovery.md
    ├── docker-network-fix.md
    ├── commands-cheatsheet.md
    └── pull-images.py
```

## Quick Reference
- Web: `http://localhost:2283`
- Start: `docker compose up -d --pull never`
- Stop: `docker compose down`
- Status: `docker ps --format 'table {{.Names}}\t{{.Status}}\t{{.Ports}}'`
- Logs: `docker compose logs -f`
- Config: `cat .env` or `docker compose config`
- Backup: `python3 backup-to-s3.py`
- Restore: `python3 restore-from-s3.py`

## Network Architecture
- Docker Desktop uses internal proxy `http.docker.internal:3128` for pulls
- Docker Hub works, ghcr.io times out on TLS handshake
- Host CAN reach ghcr.io (curl works)
- Containers CAN reach ghcr.io (wget from busybox works)
- Only Docker's pull mechanism is broken
